    <region regionID="IT-57-AP-01">
      <name>Monti Sibillini Ovest</name>
    </region>
    <region regionID="IT-57-MC-01">
      <name>Appennino Fabrianese</name>
    </region>
    <dangerRating>
      <mainValue>considerable</mainValue>
      <validTimePeriod>all_day</validTimePeriod>
    </dangerRating>
    <avalancheProblem>
      <problemType>wind_slab</problemType>
      <elevation uom="m"/>
      <aspect>NE</aspect>
      <aspect>S</aspect>
      <aspect>E</aspect>
      <aspect>NW</aspect>
      <aspect>SE</aspect>
      <aspect>N</aspect>
      <aspect>W</aspect>
      <aspect>SW</aspect>
      <validTimePeriod>all_day</validTimePeriod>
      <snowpackStability>very_poor</snowpackStability>
      <frequency>some</frequency>
      <avalancheSize>3</avalancheSize>
    </avalancheProblem>
    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>The new snow and wind slabs represent the main danger. Above approximately 1800 m the wind slabs are larger. Wind slabs are to be evaluated with care and prudence.</highlights>
      <comment>In all aspects medium-sized and, in isolated cases, large slab avalanches are possible. In particular in the regions with a lot of snow the avalanches can penetrate even deep layers. As a consequence of solar radiation a very precarious avalanche situation will be encountered in some regions.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>A lot of snow has fallen over a wide area. In some places new snow and wind slabs are lying on a moist old snowpack. The high temperatures as the day progresses will give rise to rapid moistening of the snowpack on steep sunny slopes.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
    <travelAdvisory/>
    <tendency>
      <tendencyType>increasing</tendencyType>
      <validTime>
        <startTime>2026-04-03T22:00:00Z</startTime>
        <endTime>2026-04-04T22:00:00Z</endTime>
      </validTime>
    </tendency>
    <customData>
